        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 20 at 4:02PM CST by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 4 miles southwest of Palo Duro Canyon to 8
miles northeast of Vigo Park. Movement was northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Claude, Washburn, Wayside, Palo Duro Canyon, and Goodnight.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 84 and 87.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
